  <static seed="1174" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalFunctions/reduceRationalFunction40.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ K(t) = {\frac{2t^{3}+5t^{2}}{2t^{3}+7t^{2}+5t}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>K(t)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{t}{t+1}, t\ne -2.5\hbox{ and }t\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   K(t) \amp = {\frac{2t^{3}+5t^{2}}{2t^{3}+7t^{2}+5t}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(2t+5\right)}}{{t\mathopen{}\left(2t^{2}+7t+5\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(2t+5\right)}}{{t\mathopen{}\left(2t+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{t}{t+1}, t\ne -2.5\hbox{ and }t\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The expression <m>t(2t+5)</m> was canceled. To find what values would cause the crossed out expression to be <m>0</m>, we solve the equation:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   t(2t+5) \amp = 0 \\
   t = 0 \amp \text{ or } 2t+5=0 \\
   t = 0 \amp \text{ or } 2t=-5 \\
   t = 0 \amp \text{ or } t= {-{\frac{5}{2}}} \\
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>t \ne {-{\frac{5}{2}}\; and \;0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
